  gh|about-php|/foreach.html||

}
{ array_key_exists #php-array_key_exists

 `array_key_exists($key, $ary)` returns `TRUE` if the array `$ary` contains the key `$key`. Otherwise, it returns `FALSE`.

  Note that counterintuitevly, IMHO, the first parameter is the key and the second the array!

  gh|about-php|/array/associative/key_exists.html||

  See also the function → development/web/php/snippets/variable#php-isset[`isset()`] which checks if a → development/web/php/snippets/variable[variable] is declared and different from `NULL`.

}
{ ksort

  `ksort($ary)` sorts the elements in `$ary` according to the values of their keys.

}
